# AKOS PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP Governance

Use this rule whenever authoring or amending a closure UAT report whose
`verdict:` is `PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP`. Codifies operator decision
**D-IH-86-CX** (Wave R+1 Commit 3-a mint, 2026-05-25). Mechanical
companion to [`PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar that future agents and operators
inherit by default when authoring any PWF verdict.

## When this rule applies

A UAT report is in scope for this rule when **all** of:

- The report's path matches `docs/wip/planning/**/reports/uat-*.md`.
- The report's `verdict:` frontmatter is `PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP`.
- The report's `last_review:` is ≥ 2026-05-19 (forward-only watershed
  per [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md) §"Migration posture").

Reports NOT in scope: PASS / FAIL / PENDING-OPERATOR-WALK /
FORWARD-CHARTERED verdicts (the validator no-ops). Pre-watershed
reports get INFO-only findings per the canonical's §"Migration posture".

## RULE 1 — Author the 5-class rationale block (binding)

Every in-scope UAT report MUST include the structured
`verdict_followup_rationale` block in its frontmatter:

```yaml
verdict: PASS-WITH-FOLLOWUP
verdict_followup_rationale:
  followup_class: <one of the 5 enum values from canonical §3>
  closure_target: <Wave-X close | YYYY-MM-DD | OPS-NN-N closed | D-IH-NN-X | FTW-CODE closes>
  owner: <role name from baseline_organisation.csv OR AIC:<role>>
  tracker_path: <docs/wip/planning/_trackers/<slug>.md OR _blockers/<slug>-tracker.md>  # if required by class
  closure_decision_id_target: <D-IH-NN-X if known>  # optional
  notes: <free-text context>
```

The 5 followup classes (canonical §3 enum):

1. **`monitoring-obligation`** — verdict is PASS in substance; followup
   is observation cadence.
2. **`deferred-work-with-tracker`** — concrete work scoped-out;
   tracker file under `_trackers/` required.
3. **`convention-class-followup`** — doctrinal refinement; not blocking.
4. **`mechanical-recovery-with-eta`** — known fix with ETA.
5. **`escalation-to-blocker-tracker`** — closure blocked on operator
   judgement / external dependency; tracker file under `_blockers/` required.

Worked examples for each class live in [`.cursor/skills/pwf-governance-craft/SKILL.md`](../skills/pwf-governance-craft/SKILL.md).

## RULE 2 — Use the validator at authoring time (binding)

Before committing any PWF report, run:

```powershell
py scripts/validate_pwf_governance.py --report <path> --strict
```

The validator MUST exit 0. The validator catches six failure modes via
the codes `PWF-FM-01-CLASS-MISSING` / `PWF-FM-02-CLASS-UNKNOWN` /
`PWF-FM-03-CLOSURE-TARGET-MISSING` / `PWF-FM-04-TRACKER-PATH-MISSING` /
`PWF-FM-04-TRACKER-PATH-INVALID` (all FAIL on forward-only reports) +
`PWF-FM-05-OWNER-MISSING` (WARN always).

## RULE 3 — Findings disposition via inline-ratify 5-option enum (binding)

When the validator emits a WARN or FAIL finding that the agent cannot
deterministically fix in the same authoring session, surface as an
inline `AskQuestion` gate per [`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc)
using the 5-option enum codified in
[`PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md) §6:

1. **deterministic-fix-now** (default for missing rationale fields).
2. **manual-fix-now** (default for malformed tracker_path).
3. **defer-OPS** (only acceptable for pre-watershed reports).
4. **accept-as-canon** (rare; operator ratifies non-standard shape +
   appends contra-precedent decision row).
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** (rationale gap blocked on operator
   judgement; mints `_blockers/pwf-rationale-<slug>-tracker.md` per
   [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc)).

Time-box recovery applies per `akos-inline-ratification.mdc`: 24h+
operator silence + clean validators + reversible dispositions
auto-default to the recommended option; irreversible dispositions
NEVER auto-default.

## RULE 4 — INFO→FAIL ramp posture (binding from D-IH-86-CX ratification)

Per D-IH-86-CX §4.1: the FAIL ramp activates on the **2026-05-19
watershed** (same date as UAT_DISCIPLINE per D-IH-86-AS). Reports with
`last_review` before that date get INFO findings only — migration-grace
window.

The validator stays at INFO ramp (release-gate advisory) until **Wave T
close** at the earliest, and only promotes to FAIL when all three
conditions hold:

1. The Wave R UAT amendment closes (Commit 3-c per parent workspace
   plan), supplying the structural rationale the validator currently
   catches.
2. Three consecutive wave-close sweeps emit zero forward-only FAIL
   findings.
3. Operator-explicit decision row (D-IH-86-CX-V2 or successor) records
   the promotion.

## RULE 5 — Specialty mint contract (binding)

When this rule itself was minted (Wave R+1 Commit 3-a), it followed
the same 15-surface contract that the Wave M INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION +
Wave N INDEX_INTEGRITY precedent established:

1. Canonical doctrine: `docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUP_GOVERNANCE_DISCIPLINE.md`.
2. Pydantic chassis: `akos/hlk_pwf_governance.py`.
3. Validator: `scripts/validate_pwf_governance.py`.
4. Runbook: same script (validator IS runbook — check-class only).
5. Cursor rule: `.cursor/rules/akos-pwf-governance.mdc` (this file).
6. Skill: `.cursor/skills/pwf-governance-craft/SKILL.md`.
7. Paired SOP: `SOP-PEOPLE_PWF_GOVERNANCE_001.md`.
8. PEOPLE_DESIGN_PATTERN_REGISTRY row: `pattern_pwf_governance_discipline`.
9. PRECEDENCE.md canonical + mirror rows.
10. HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md §6 specialty list row.
11. CHANGELOG.md entry citing D-IH-86-CX.
12. `process_list.csv` row: `hol_peopl_dtp_pwf_governance_001`.
13. `validate_hlk.py` umbrella dispatcher row.
14. `config/verification-profiles.json` `pre_commit` step: `validate_pwf_governance_self_test`.
15. `scripts/release-gate.py` advisory wiring: `run_pwf_governance_validation`.

All 15 surfaces land in the same atomic commit so the specialty is
operationally complete before being advertised. The Wave R+1 Commit
3-a is the worked example.

## RULE 6 — Compose multiplicatively with UAT_DISCIPLINE (binding)

PWF governance is the **content axis** of closure UAT discipline; the
**classification axis** lives in [`UAT_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/UAT_DISCIPLINE.md).
A UAT report passes governance only when **BOTH** validators pass:

```text
validate_uat_report.py  → catches UAT-FM-11 (PWF verdict + empty rationale)
                       + classification-axis findings (UAT-FM-01..10)

validate_pwf_governance.py → catches structural rationale gaps (PWF-FM-01..05)
                          when rationale is non-empty but malformed
```

The two validators compose multiplicatively per
[`HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/HOLISTIKA_QUALITY_FABRIC.md) §3 (the
load-bearing multiplicative-AND rule). Neither validator's PASS
substitutes for the other.

## When this rule does NOT apply

- **PASS / FAIL / PENDING / FORWARD-CHARTERED verdicts** — the
  validator no-ops; this rule does not fire.
- **Pre-watershed reports** (`last_review` < 2026-05-19) — INFO-only;
  closure never blocked.
- **Non-UAT artifacts** — phase reports, ratification artifacts,
  pre-pause records do not (yet) carry PWF-shaped verdicts; forward-
  charter pointer in the canonical's §2 scope.
- **Chore-only single-commit waves** — exempt entirely (no closure
  UAT required).

